<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-01T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-01T17:00:00-05:00" n="484" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d484">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">882.77/31: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bundy</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-01T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">October
                                            1, 1919, 6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your September 25, 2 p.m.</p>
                            <p>You may suggest to Liberian Government that for the present and until
                                the conclusion of loan agreement negotiations they may not wish to
                                give definite consideration to such applications.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>